title: Grateful Dead Live at The Centrum on 1987-04-04
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.8 MHz) >KORG AudioGate 4 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Touch Of Gray-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Althea, El Paso, Tennessee Jed, Cassidy, Good Time Blues, Box Of Rain, Promised Land

Set 2

Iko Iko, Playin' In The Band-> Comes A Time-> Hand Jive-> Drums-> Space-> Truckin'-> Playin' In The Band-> Morning Dew, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text:
Best Sound This is the best sound of this show, by far. Yes, there are little FM clips here and there, but on the whole, excellent, well-balanced sound.

I've always loved the FM recordings as they were Matrix right out of the gate. There's some bombastic audience, but then there's a deeper ambiance and richer bass than heard on the board. This really captures the audience experience well.

This was a fun three-night run, for sure. We crashed at a friend-of-a-friend's lake camp after N1, and stuck close to the Centrum via a Clark U dorm invasion the next two nights. Such pandemonium!

This is a super high energy performance, for sure. Compact 87 1-2 punchin'; a bit light on the spacier jams, but rockin' and rollin' for sure.
Excellent Recording I was there 35 years ago today. The 3 shows were absolutely amazing, and I am so glad I lived close enough to attend all 3.
